{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "ClientSide Ecommerce API",
    "description": "Storefront API (2026-04): health, OTP auth, Google OAuth2 + JWT exchange, profile, service area, catalog, storefront cart/checkout/account/orders.\n\n**Tenant / shop**\n- Send **`x-shop-id: {{shopId}}`** on tenant-scoped routes (catalog, storefront, checkout, …). Query parameters **`shopId`** / **`shop_id`** are not read for resolution.\n\n**Setup**\n- `npm run dev` — default **4100**. `npm run db:migrate`. A **shop** row must exist; set **`shopId`** (collection or environment variable).\n- **`.env`:** `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `API_PUBLIC_URL`, Google OAuth vars. Redirect URI in Google Console: `{API_PUBLIC_URL}/api/oauth/callback/google`.\n\n**JWT**\n- **`POST /api/auth/otp/verify`** and **`POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt`** return **`accessToken`**.\n- Protected routes: `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`.\n\n**Postman + OAuth JWT exchange**\n- Cookie flow: after browser Google callback to `/api/oauth/callback/google`, cookie **`storefront_oauth_exchange`** is set on API host.\n- `POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt` with body `{}` succeeds only when valid cookie is sent.\n\n**Architecture note**\n- Picker/staff APIs are not served by this app anymore; picker notifications are handled by a separate server/process.\n\n**CORS**\n- API allows credentials for **`CORS_ORIGIN`** (e.g. `http://localhost:5173`). OAuth `POST /api/oauth/sign-in/social` may need **`Origin`** matching that value when testing from CLI.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4100" },
    { "key": "shopId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "phone", "value": "+919999999999" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "corsOrigin", "value": "http://localhost:5173" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/",
            "description": "Service stub: `ok`, `service`, links to `/health`, `/openapi.json`, and `/api-docs`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
            "description": "Liveness: `status`, `service`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/otp/request",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"{{phone}}\",\n  \"shopId\": \"{{shopId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/otp/request",
            "description": "Request an OTP for a phone number + shop."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/otp/verify",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "  if (j.shopIds && j.shopIds[0]) pm.collectionVariables.set('shopId', j.shopIds[0]);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"{{phone}}\",\n  \"shopId\": \"{{shopId}}\",\n  \"code\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/otp/verify",
            "description": "Verify OTP and issue customer JWT."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt (body {})",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "  if (j.shopIds && j.shopIds[0]) pm.collectionVariables.set('shopId', j.shopIds[0]);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/oauth/jwt",
            "description": "After Google callback, exchange `storefront_oauth_exchange` cookie for JWT. Body `{}` is valid.\n\nRequires a valid cookie; returns **401** if cookie is missing/invalid."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "OAuth (Google)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/oauth/callback/google (browser only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/oauth/callback/google?code=PASTE_CODE&state=PASTE_STATE",
            "description": "Google redirects here with **`code`** and **`state`**. Not useful to run manually in Postman unless you paste real OAuth params immediately after redirect. On success sets **`storefront_oauth_exchange`** cookie."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/oauth/sign-in/social",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Origin", "value": "{{corsOrigin}}" },
              { "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"provider\": \"google\",\n  \"disableRedirect\": true,\n  \"callbackURL\": \"{{baseUrl}}/\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/oauth/sign-in/social",
            "description": "**`disableRedirect: true`** — **200** `{ \"url\" }` for opening Google in browser.\n\nOmit **`disableRedirect`** for **302** redirect (browser + cookie state).\n\nTenant: **`x-shop-id`** header (preferred) or **`additionalData.shopId`** (header wins if both sent).\n\n**503** if Google OAuth env missing."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Profile",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/me/profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me/profile",
            "description": "**401** without `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "PATCH /api/me/profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"displayName\": \"Updated Name\",\n  \"address\": {\n    \"line1\": \"10 Example Street\",\n    \"city\": \"London\",\n    \"postalCode\": \"SW1A 1AA\",\n    \"country\": \"GB\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me/profile",
            "description": "Partial update. Do not send **`address: {}`** (validation error). Address fields use API camelCase (`postalCode`, …)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Serviceability",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /storefront/location/check",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"lat\": 12.9716,\n  \"lng\": 77.5946\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/storefront/location/check",
            "description": "**200** — `serviceable`, `distanceM`, `maxRadiusM`. Uses tenant from `x-shop-id` (or host resolution)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Catalog",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/search",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/search?type=both&q=&categoryId=&parentId=&availability=&productSort=name&productOrder=asc&categorySort=sort_order&categoryOrder=asc&productLimit=100&productOffset=0&categoryLimit=500&categoryOffset=0",
            "description": "Requires **`x-shop-id`** (or host-based shop resolution).\n\n**type:** `products` | `categories` | `both`.\n\n**q:** optional search (name/slug).\n\nProducts: `categoryId`, `availability`, `productSort`, `productOrder`, `productLimit`, `productOffset`.\n\nCategories: `parentId`, `categorySort`, `categoryOrder`, `categoryLimit`, `categoryOffset`.\n\n**200:** `{ products, categories }` (arrays may be omitted when filtered)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/categories",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/categories",
            "description": "Root categories. Optional **`parentId`** (UUID) for children."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/products",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/products",
            "description": "Active products. Optional **`categoryId`**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/catalog/items",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "x-shop-id", "value": "{{shopId}}" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/items",
            "description": "Same as **products** (active items)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
